{- Bind x to true or false arbitrarily Bind y to 2 or 3 Note that in the Orc calculus y will always be bound to 2 since Rtimer(2) always publishes before Rtimer(3) and combinators/publications occur instantaneously. However, depending on the real world implementation and hardware of distributed executions of Orc it is possible that y may be bound to 3. -}
val x = true | false val y = Rtimer(2) >> 2 | Rtimer(3) >> 3
